{"type":"message","id":"f37bbfb3","parentId":"ac0aefc7","timestamp":"2026-05-28T03:46:21.610Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I just realized - running this headed will open a Chromium window on the server machine. The user won't see it. Let me think about whether this will actually work on the server...\n\nAlso, looking at the TAPD detail page, the edit might not be a standard button. It could be an icon. Let me try a different approach altogether - maybe I can just use the API directly?\n\nActually, TAPD does have an API. But using the TAPD API for attachments is more complex. Let me just try running the headed browser script. If it fails, I'll try the API approach.\n\nActually, let me take a step back. The problem with the edit page was:\n1. Headless: WAF blocked\n2. Headed: timeout on `networkidle`\n\nMaybe I should just go to the detail page first (which we know works from the create flow), then use the TAPD API to add attachments. TAPD has a public API.\n\nActually, looking at the previous successfully created bug - the `createBug` function worked fine in headless mode. So the cookie is valid. The issue was just the edit page URL / the `networkidle` timeout.\n\nLet me just simplify: go to the detail page, then try to click around to find edit and file upload. In headed mode it should work since createBug's headed approach worked.\n\nWait, `createBug` actually uses `headless: true` with the stealth init script. Let me check...\n\nLooking at the SKILL.md, it says: \n1. Headless mode (preferred): Apply stealth init script\n2. Headed mode (fallback): headless: false\n\nAnd the create_bug.mjs script uses headless by default with the stealth script.\n\nLet me look at how the create page works - the create page (`/bugs/add`) was loaded fine in the `createBug` function. The issue might be specific to the edit URL.\n\nLet me try a simpler approach: go directly to the create page and re-upload, or just fetch the page source