{"type":"message","id":"75cf7bf0","parentId":"e3338acd","timestamp":"2026-05-28T03:47:40.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cookies are expired. Even after visiting `www.tapd.cn`, we still got redirected to login. This means the `tapdsession` cookie is no longer valid. The cookie was from the previous keepalive run and has expired.\n\nI need to do the TAPD login flow. Let me think about how to handle this.\n\nFrom MEMORY.md:\n- 失效救援：检测到 cookie 失效时，用 `headless: false` 跑 Playwright，访问 `https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login`，点微信扫码，让主人扫一下，然后保存新 cookie\n\nBut that's the fallback when keepalive fails. Let me first check if the tapd keepalive script needs to be run, or if the cookies are just stale.\n\nActually, let me check if the cookies I have are for the right account. I'm using `tapd_cookies.json` which should be 周以天 (from MEMORY.md). But also the keepalive might not have run recently enough.\n\nLet me try running the keepalive script first. If that doesn't work, I'll need the user to scan the QR code.\n\nActually, let me check what time the keepalive was last run.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Cookie 过期了，先跑保活续期。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_EzwES8C1Z8sspU3pz13O7765","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs","timeout":60,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":15000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":332,"output":392,"cacheRead":56320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57044,"cost":{"input":0.00004648,"output":0.00010976,"cacheRead":0.0015769599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0017331999999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779940055719,"responseId":"5c819da5-86b4-4e51-a178-6d0afaebf46b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"97c029b1","parentId":"75cf7bf0","timestamp":"2026-05-28T03:47:45.230Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_EzwES8C1Z8sspU3pz13O7765","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[2026-05-28T03:47:40.685Z] [周以天] Loaded 15 cookies\n[2026-05-28T03:47:40.889Z] [周以天] Visiting workspace dashboard...\n[2026-05-28T03:47:45.089Z] [周以天] HTTP 200 | url=https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login?site=TAPD&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tapd.cn%2F31253609%2F | title=登录-TAPD\n[2026-05-28T03:47:45.090Z] [周以天] Session EXPIRED - need re-login\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":4903,"aggregated":"[2026-05-28T03:47:40.685Z] [周以天] Loaded 15 cookies\n[2026-05-28T03:47:40.889Z] [周以天] Visiting workspace dashboard...\n[2026-05-28T03:47:45.089Z] [周以天] HTTP 200 | url=https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login?site=TAPD&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tapd.cn%2F31253609%2F | title=登录-TAPD\n[2026-05-28T03:47:45.090Z] [周以天] Session EXPIRED - need re-login\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779940065230}}
{"type":"message","id":"170a3c29","parentId":"97c029b1","timestamp":"2026-05-28T03:47:56.649Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tapd cookie for 周以天 has expired. I need to do the re-login flow. According to MEMORY.md:\n\n> **失效救援：** 检测到 cookie 失效时，用 `headless: false` 跑 Playwright，访问 `https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login`，点微信扫码，让主人扫一下，然后保存新 cookie\n\nI need to open TAPD in headed mode, show the QR code, and ask the user to scan it. But this is a headless server environment... hmm.\n\nWait, the user is on the other end (Feishu chat). They can't see the browser window. So I need to somehow show the QR code to the user.\n\nLet me think about this differently. I can:\n1. Take a screenshot of the QR code\n2. Send it to the user via Feishu\n3. Ask them to scan it with WeChat\n4. Then save the new cookies\n\nOR I could just use 叶枝君's cookie (since it might still be valid). The bug was created normally using createBug which uses the same cookies file. Wait, the createBug succeeded earlier! How?\n\nLet me check - the createBug script was running with the same cookies file and it worked. Both the `createBug` script and my attach script use the same `tapd_cookies.json`. Let me see if maybe there's a difference in the stealth script or approach.\n\nActually wait, maybe the issue is specific to the edit page vs the create page. The `www.tapd.cn` site might have separate handling for `bugs/add` vs `bugs/edit`. Or maybe the session expired very recently (between when the bug was created and now).\n\nLet me check the timing. The bug was created successfully in the previous turn. Now in this turn, the cookie expired. This could mean the session actually was valid but just very short-lived, or the edit page specifically checks something different.\n\nLet me try again to access the create page (which worked before) just to check if the cookie is still valid for that specific page.\n\nActually, let me just go through the QR code login flow. That's the proper fallback. I'll:\n1. Launch headed browser to TAPD login page\n2. Take a screenshot of the QR code\n3. Send it to the user and ask them to scan\n4. Wait for them to confirm\n5. Save the cookies\n6. Then upload the attachment\n\nLet me write a script for this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Cookie 过期了，我打开 TAPD 扫码页，主人扫一下码重新登录，然后继续上传。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_oawA57Uo44D6oaXYwpwP8280","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\temp_tapd_relogin.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nconst WS_DIR = path.resolve(__dirname, '..');\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies.json');\nconst LOGIN_URL = 'https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login';\n\n(async () => {\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: false });\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\n  \n  await page.goto(LOGIN_URL, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  \n  console.log('Page URL:', page.url());\n  console.log('Title:', await page.title());\n  \n  // Take screenshot of QR code\n  await page.screenshot({ path: path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_qrcode.png'), fullPage: false });\n  console.log('QR code screenshot saved to tapd_qrcode.png');\n  \n  // Wait for login - user should scan the QR code\n  console.log('Waiting for user to scan QR code and login...');\n  \n  // Poll until we're redirected away from login page\n  let loggedIn = false;\n  for (let i = 0; i < 120; i++) { // wait up to 2 minutes\n    await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n    const url = page.url();\n    if (!url.includes('login') && !url.includes('cloud_logins')) {\n      loggedIn = true;\n      console.log('Login detected! Current URL:', url);\n      break;\n    }\n  }\n  \n  if (!loggedIn) {\n    console.log('Login timeout');\n    await browser.close();\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n  \n  // Save cookies\n  const cookies = await page.context().cookies();\n  fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, JSON.stringify(cookies, null, 2));\n  console.log('Cookies saved to', COOKIES_FILE);\n  \n  await browser.close();\n  console.log('RELOGIN_SUCCESS');\n})().catch(e => { console.error('ERROR:', e.message || e); process.exit(1); });\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":265,"output":1122,"cacheRead":56960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58347,"cost":{"input":0.0000371,"output":0.00031416,"cacheRead":0.00159488,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019461399999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779940065232,"responseId":"7b138751-d3cc-4015-92b8-e62f9c02d7d4"}}
