{"type":"message","id":"db224f87","parentId":"847d05b6","timestamp":"2026-05-28T03:49:28.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, wait - I realize a potential issue. The `tryLogin` function clears cookies when called the second time because it adds cookies to the same context. Let me fix this by using separate contexts or clearing cookies between attempts.\n\nActually, looking at the code - `context.addCookies(cookies)` adds cookies to the existing context. So if yezhijun's cookies fail (because they're expired), and then I add zhouyitian's cookies on top, the expired cookies are still there. Let me refactor.\n\nActually, let me just try both and check. If the first fails, I'll close the browser and start fresh with the second set.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_33MxUrmNrYoPEGIaSf7S5302","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\temp_attach_bug_v3.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"  // Try yezhijun cookies first\n  let loggedIn = await tryLogin(context, page, path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies_yezhijun.json'));\n  \n  if (!loggedIn) {\n    console.log('yezhijun cookies expired, trying zhouyitian...');\n    loggedIn = await tryLogin(context, page, path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies.json'));\n  }","newText":"  // Try yezhijun cookies first\n  let loggedIn = await tryLogin(context, page, path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies_yezhijun.json'));\n  \n  if (!loggedIn) {\n    console.log('yezhijun cookies expired, trying zhouyitian...');\n    await context.clearCookies();\n    loggedIn = await tryLogin(context, page, path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies.json'));\n  }"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":102,"output":451,"cacheRead":61312,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61865,"cost":{"input":0.00001428,"output":0.00012628000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001716736,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001857296}},"stopReason