{"type":"message","id":"5316484e","parentId":"06659e3d","timestamp":"2026-05-28T04:00:52.189Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The TAPD login page is behind a WAF/403 block page when accessed headlessly. The QR code that showed earlier was when running in headed mode. The WAF blocks headless browser access to the login page.\n\nSo I need to use headed mode (`headless: false`) to access TAPD. The previous QR code screenshot was from a headed browser session.\n\nLet me check the screenshot to see what the page looks like. Actually, I can't view it easily right now. But the key point is:\n1. Headless → WAF blocks → 403 page\n2. Headed → WAF allows → shows login page (QR code or password login)\n\nSo I need to run in headed mode. Let me write a script that:\n1. Opens the login page in headed mode\n2. Clicks the password login tab\n3. Fills in credentials\n4. Submits\n5. Saves cookies\n6. Uploads the attachment\n\nLet me check if the login page has a password login option. Let me run the check script in headed mode.\n\nActually, let me just look at the debug_login_page.png screenshot first to understand the page layout.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_J39dmoKWXGD4bpPU3Xs87385","name":"image","arguments":{"image":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\debug_login_page.png","prompt":"What does this page show? Is there a WAF/403 block or the actual TAPD login page? Can you see any login form, QR code, or tabs for switching login methods?"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":402,"output":360,"cacheRead":73600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74362,"cost":{"input":0.00005628,"output":0.00010080000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0020608,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0022178799999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779940847565,"responseId":"a4b905e9-1c6c-47a0-8675-714763797ef6"}}
