{"type":"message","id":"c8c901e1","parentId":"b6822175","timestamp":"2026-05-28T05:56:44.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK now let me take a practical approach. Looking at the TAPD login flow:\n\n1. The form has `action=\"https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login\"` with method POST\n2. Password is encrypted before sending (`via=encrypt_password`)\n3. Tencent CAPTCHA is required but the captcha element was NOT found (`Captcha element found: false`) on the initial page load\n4. There's a `login_precheck` API\n\nKey insight: the captcha might only appear after certain conditions are met (e.g., too many failed attempts, or the precheck determines it's necessary).\n\nLet me try:\n1. Fill in the form with username and password\n2. Click the \"协议\" checkbox  \n3. Press Enter on the password field to trigger form submission\n4. The JS should handle encryption and captcha flow\n\nBut wait - I noticed earlier that the form was submitted but stayed on the login page. This means the server rejected it (likely due to captcha or password encryption).\n\nActually, I think the real issue is simpler. Let me look at what `login_precheck` returns. The precheck endpoint received `email=18068135880`. If the precheck determines that this account requires captcha, it will set up the captcha flow.\n\nLet me try a more comprehensive approach:\n1. Fill in the form\n2. Use `page.keyboard.press('Enter')` on the password field\n3. Wait and check if any captcha appears\n4. If captcha appears, we know the issue\n5. If not, check the network response\n\nWait, I also noticed that the `encrypt_key` and `encrypt_iv` are empty. The AES encryption requires these. Let me look at what generates them.\n\nThe flow might be:\n1. User clicks login/precheck\n2. Server returns encrypt_key and encrypt_iv\n3. Client encrypts the password with these\n4. Client initializes captcha\n5. User solves captcha\n6. Form is submitted with encrypted password + captcha ticket\n\nThis is complex to automate. Let me try a different approach entirely.\n\nLet me see if I can use the TAPD API directly. TAPD has a REST API documented at https://www.tapd.cn/help/view/112327. But this requires API tokens, not session cookies.\n\nLet me just try pressing Enter on the password field to see if that triggers the login JS properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FpWodVOuvxrdiTyqwv5D5453","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\tapd_login_v2.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nconst WS_DIR = path.resolve(__dirname, '..');\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies.json');\nconst COOKIES_BAK = path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies_zhouyitian.json');\nconst WORKSPACE_ID = '31253609';\nconst BUG_ID = '1131253609001016781';\nconst VIDEO_PATH = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\media\\\\inbound\\\\033673d511f35b9b52f8d783e45421aa---751e504b-76c9-4234-96f7-3adcc6ed0aec.mp4';\nconst PHONE = '18068135880';\nconst PASSWORD = 'Hanji2002731';\n\n(async () => {\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: false });\n  const page = await browser.newPage({ viewport: { width: 1280, height: 900 } });\n\n  await page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login', { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n\n  // Click password tab\n  await page.locator('.login-tab-password').click();\n  await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n\n  // Fill\n  await page.locator('#username').fill(PHONE);\n  await page.locator('#password_input').fill(PASSWORD);\n\n  // Check agreement\n  await page.evaluate(() => { \n    const cb = document.querySelector('#protocol-checkbox');\n    if (cb) cb.checked = true;\n  });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(500);\n\n  // Press Enter on password field to trigger login\n  console.log('Pressing Enter on password field...');\n  await page.locator('#password_input').press('Enter');\n\n  // Wait for redirect\n  await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n  \n  for (let i = 0; i < 40; i++) {\n    const url = page.url();\n    console.log(`Check ${i}: URL=${url.substring(0, 100)}`);\n    \n    if (!url.includes('login') && !url.includes('cloud_logins')) {\n      console.log('LOGIN SUCCESS!');\n      \n      // Save cookies\n      const cookies = await page.context().cookies();\n      fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, JSON.stringify(cookies, null, 2));\n      fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_BAK, JSON.stringify(cookies, null, 2));\n      console.log(`Cookies saved (${cookies.length})`);\n      \n      // Upload attachment\n      const editUrl = `https://www.tapd.cn/${WORKSPACE_ID}/bugtrace/bugs/edit?id=${BUG_ID}`;\n      console.log('Opening bug edit page...');\n      await page.goto(editUrl, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 });\n      await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n      \n      if (!page.url().includes('login')) {\n        const uploadBtn = page.locator('#upload-attachement');\n        if (await uploadBtn.count() > 0) {\n          await uploadBtn.first().click();\n          await page.waitForTimeout(1500);\n        }\n        await page.locator('#file_input').first().setInputFiles(VIDEO_PATH);\n        console.log('File set, waiting 10s...');\n        await page.waitForTimeout(10000);\n        \n        const saveBtn = page.locator('#save_return, #_view, #save_view');\n        if (await saveBtn.count() > 0) {\n          await saveBtn.first().click();\n        } else {\n          await page.evaluate(() => document.getElementById('bug_form')?.submit());\n        }\n        await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n        console.log('Bug updated! Final URL:', page.url());\n      }\n      \n      await browser.close();\n      console.log('ALL DONE');\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    // Check for captcha or other interactive elements\n    const body = await page.evaluate(() => document.body.textContent?.substring(0, 200));\n    if (body?.includes('验证') || body?.includes('captcha') || body?.includes('滑块')) {\n      console.log('Captcha detected! Body:', body?.substring(0, 100));\n    }\n    \n    await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n  }\n  \n  // If we get here, login might have failed due to captcha\n  await page.screenshot({ path: path.join(WS_DIR, 'debug_login_final.png'), fullPage: false });\n  console.log('Login failed after retries, screenshot saved');\n  console.log('Final URL:', page.url());\n  await browser.close();\n  process.exit(1);\n})();\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":91,"output":1678,"cacheRead":96512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98281,"cost":{"input":0.000012740000000000002,"output":0.00046984,"cacheRead":0.002702336,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0031849160000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779947790486,"responseId":"b3252899-560f-41e9-8971-817cc9fb3855"}}
