{"type":"message","id":"8ee20d8b","parentId":"d44c84ed","timestamp":"2026-05-28T05:57:05.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I think I should take a completely different approach. Rather than fighting with TAPD's captcha, let me see if I can use TAPD's API directly with HTTP basic auth or OAuth. \n\nActually, looking at the form more carefully, TAPD has a `login_precheck` API. Maybe the password doesn't need encryption if I send to the right endpoint.\n\nBut actually, let me just try the simplest thing that might work: use `page.fill` and then `page.locator('#password_input').press('Enter')`. The Enter key should trigger the form's submit handler which is prepared to handle captcha, encryption, etc.\n\nActually, looking back at my first attempt with `tapd_full_login_attach.mjs`, the issue was that I used `form.submit()` which bypasses the JS handlers. When the user presses Enter on the password field, the JS handlers should fire properly.\n\nLet me just try running the current script and see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tX9sXCqB72fB4wUj0Kzm5163","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts/tapd_login_v2.mjs","timeout":180,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":15000,"background":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1720,"output":339,"cacheRead":98304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100363,"cost":{"input":0.00024080000000000003,"output":0.00009492,"cacheRead":0.002752512,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0030882319999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779947820488,"responseId":"b32b0e6f-1c0e-47f2-ae5c-b2f2aa83965c"}}
