{"type":"message","id":"f8898378","parentId":"38d9b578","timestamp":"2026-05-28T05:58:01.702Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, this script uses readline which interacts with stdin. But I'm not running this interactively - it's running on the server. And the user is talking to me via Feishu chat, not directly to the script's stdin.\n\nLet me rethink this. Instead of a script that waits for stdin, I should:\n1. Send the SMS\n2. Ask the user for the code via Feishu\n3. Wait for their reply\n4. Then enter the code\n\nSo I need to split this into two parts:\n1. Part 1: Open browser, click SMS tab, enter phone, click \"获取验证码\", take screenshot to confirm, then wait\n2. User tells me the code via chat\n3. Part 2: Enter the code, submit, upload attachment\n\nActually, I can just run the script in two steps. But the script needs to keep the browser alive between steps. Or I can store the browser context.\n\nActually, let me simplify. Let me first just send the SMS code. I'll run a quick script that:\n1. Opens TAPD login\n2. Enters phone number\n3. Clicks \"获取验证码\"\n4. Keeps the browser open\n\nThen I'll ask the user for the code. When they reply, I'll continue with the code entry and upload.\n\nActually, this is getting complex with async browser management. Let me take a different, simpler approach:\n\nLet me just run the SMS script and have it wait for the code. The script will run in the background with `yieldMs`. When the user replies with the code, I'll need to somehow get it to the script.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: I'll run the script that sends the SMS first and keeps the browser alive. Then I'll ask the user for the code via chat. When they reply, I'll kill the first script and run a new one that continues.\n\nOr wait - let me use a file-based IPC. The script writes to a file when it's ready for the code, and I can write the code to a file that the script reads.\n\nActually even simpler - let me just send the SMS first (run a quick script), then ask the user. When they reply with the code, I'll run the second script.\n\nLet me write two scripts: one for sending SMS, one for entering code.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_HJavNZeYtttT0yMzk42E6198","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\step1_send_sms.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nconst PHONE = '18068135880';\n\n(async () => {\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: false });\n  const page = await browser.newPage({ viewport: { width: 1280, height: 900 } });\n\n  await page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login', { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n\n  // Use SMS tab (should be default)\n  const smsTab = page.locator('.login-tab-sms');\n  if (await smsTab.count() > 0) {\n    await smsTab.click();\n    await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n  }\n\n  // Fill phone\n  await page.locator('#phone-num').fill(PHONE);\n  console.log('Phone filled');\n\n  // Click \"获取验证码\"\n  console.log('Clicking 获取验证码...');\n  await page.locator('#mobile-sms-verify-btn').click();\n  await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n\n  console.log('SMS sent! Enter the code in the script file step2_enter_code.mjs and run it.');\n  console.log('Keeping browser alive for 120s...');\n\n  // Write browser session info to a temp file\n  const { execSync } = await import('child_process');\n  const wsEndpoint = browser.contexts()[0]?.browser?.wsEndpoint?.();\n\n  // Save browser info\n  const fs = await import('fs');\n  const path = await import('path');\n  const __dirname = path.dirname(new URL(import.meta.url).pathname);\n  fs.writeFileSync(path.join(__dirname, '..', 'temp_browser_info.json'), JSON.stringify({\n    wsEndpoint: browser.wsEndpoint(),\n    pid: process.pid,\n  }));\n\n  // Wait 2 minutes for the code\n  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 120000));\n  await browser.close();\n  console.log('Browser closed.');\n})();\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":109,"output":1010,"cacheRead":106240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107359,"cost":{"input":0.00001526,"output":0.00028280000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0029747199999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00327278}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779947872005,"responseId":"f7e5235f-ff9e-48f7-bf5e-258cf07b26fa"}}
