{"type":"message","id":"5e11b748","parentId":"01abce3b","timestamp":"2026-05-28T06:06:28.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_RVZhyKMT871Pqajr9T435002","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.7 (eeef486) — Somewhere between 'hello world' and 'oh god what have I built.'\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Fallback-deliver final text to a chat (default: false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO with offset, or +duration). Use\n                         --tz for offset-less datetimes\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last|<channel-id>) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Fallback-delivers final\n                         text to a chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable runner fallback delivery\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh)\n  --thread-id <id>       Telegram forum topic thread id\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token ***        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tools <list>         Tool allow-list (e.g. exec,read,write or exec read\n                         write)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA; cron default:\n                         Gateway host local timezone) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1580,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.7 (eeef486) — Somewhere between 'hello world' and 'oh god what have I built.'\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Fallback-deliver final text to a chat (default: false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO with offset, or +duration). Use\n                         --tz for offset-less datetimes\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last|<channel-id>) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Fallback-delivers final\n                         text to a chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable runner fallback delivery\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh)\n  --thread-id <id>       Telegram forum topic thread id\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tools <list>         Tool allow-list (e.g. exec,read,write or exec read\n                         write)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA; cron default:\n                         Gateway host local timezone) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779948388491}}
{"type":"message","id":"64b2de5f","parentId":"5e11b748","timestamp":"2026-05-28T06:06:35.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know how to add a cron job. I'll create a cron job that runs the tapd keepalive script daily for both accounts.\n\nFor the cron job:\n- For 周以天: `node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs` (default, runs daily)\n- For 叶枝君: `node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs yezhijun` (runs daily)\n\nActually, how do I set cron for exec commands? The cron job seems to be for sending agent messages, not running exec scripts. Let me check if there's a way to run a shell command via cron.\n\nLooking at the options:\n- `--message <text>` - agent message payload\n- `--session (main|isolated)`\n- `--tools <list>` - tool allow-list\n\nSo the cron triggers an agent session with a message. The message would be something like \"run TAPD keepalive\" and the agent would execute it.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is to add two cron jobs:\n1. One that sends a system event to main session to trigger TAPD 周以天 keepalive\n2. One for 叶枝君\n\nBut actually, these cron jobs need to exec shell commands. I should use `--session isolated` to run in an isolated session, and the message should tell the agent to run the keepalive script.\n\nWait, actually, I could use `--message \"run the script node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs\"` and allow the exec tool. But that's a bit roundabout.\n\nLet me check if there's a direct way to exec a command via cron.\n\nActually, looking at the cron system more carefully, I think the best approach would be to have the cron job send a message to an isolated session that then runs the keepalive script. I'll need to specify `--tools exec` so the agent can run commands.\n\nLet me add the cron jobs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_edAXWvf59UFi6JGuQfFx9176","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add --name \"tapd-keepalive-zhouyitian\" --cron \"0 10 * * *\" --m